# Example udev rules for stable OVEN serial aliases.
# Copy to /etc/udev/rules.d/99-owen-serial.rules and replace the values below
# with the actual attributes from:
#   udevadm info -a -n /dev/ttyACM2
#
# Typical workflow:
# 1. Find the needed USB serial interface in /dev/serial/by-id
# 2. Inspect its attributes with udevadm
# 3. Create a readable stable alias such as /dev/owen-line1
#
# Example for one interface of a WCH USB Quad Serial adapter:
# SUBSYSTEM=="tty", \
#   ATTRS{idVendor}=="1a86", \
#   ATTRS{idProduct}=="55d4", \
#   ATTRS{serial}=="BCD91DABCD", \
#   ENV{ID_USB_INTERFACE_NUM}=="04", \
#   SYMLINK+="owen-line1"
#
# Second line example:
# SUBSYSTEM=="tty", \
#   ATTRS{idVendor}=="1a86", \
#   ATTRS{idProduct}=="55d4", \
#   ATTRS{serial}=="BCD91DABCD", \
#   ENV{ID_USB_INTERFACE_NUM}=="02", \
#   SYMLINK+="owen-line2"
